// Upload — companion config for UPLOADED_FILE / UPLOADED_IMAGE
// fields. The gateway resolves `connection` to a KV-capability
// connection in the same domain, computes the final storage key
// from `bucket_path` + a hash-based sub-bucket prefix derived from
// `expected_objects` / `max_per_bucket`, streams the inbound
// multipart file part through a tmp file, hashes during write,
// then atomically moves the result under that key.
//
// Sub-bucket depth derivation:
//
//	depth = ceil(log_max_per_bucket(expected_objects))
//
// Final layout:
//
//	<bucket_path>/<sub_bucket_path>/<object_key>
//
// where sub_bucket_path is `<2 hex chars>/<2 hex chars>/...` taken
// from the first `2*depth` chars of sha256(object_key). Hash-based
// distribution is the only mode in MVP (uniform spread); sequential
// bucketing is a future opt-in.
